chapters.title: as economies recover from pandemic losses
The Eurozone annual inflation rate surged
Energy costs were hit the hardest by rising inflation
The highest annual inflation rates across Eurozone members
Europe's energy sector is dominated by natural gas
with rising numbers of people working from home
Although, the most significant sources of natural gas for Europe
contributed to the rising gas prices
Furthermore, economies faced a worldwide chip shortage crisis
